The user is likely using RBesT to derive a mixture prior of the object type mixbeta for the response rate of a cohort on the probability scale, which would then need to be translated to the logit (aka log odds) scale by sampling from the mixbeta object, applying the logit transformation, and fitting a mixnorm object to the transformed sample. The mixnorm object is then to be fed into performAnalyses as prior information. 
 
